# HTML Conversion & Assets

## HTML pages

- Journal Pages use `type: "text"` with `text.format: 1` (HTML).
- Wrap content in `<div class="pdf2foundry">…</div>` to scope CSS.
- Use semantic tags: h1–h4, p, ul/ol, table, figure/figcaption, img, code/pre.
- Add stable anchors for section headings when helpful.

## Images

- Extract images unchanged into `assets/`.
- Reference images via `modules/<mod-id>/assets/<name>` inside HTML.

## Tables

- Try Camelot (lattice/stream) to generate real `<table>` when possible.
- If uncertain or failing, rasterize the region and embed as `<img>`.

## CSS

- Provide `styles/pdf2foundry.css` with safe, minimal rules, e.g.:

```css
.pdf2foundry h1, .pdf2foundry h2, .pdf2foundry h3 { margin-top: 0.6em; }
.pdf2foundry figure { margin: 1em 0; text-align: center; }
.pdf2foundry figcaption { font-size: 0.9em; opacity: 0.8; }
.pdf2foundry img { max-width: 100%; height: auto; }
```

## Links

- Internal: `@UUID[JournalEntry.<entryId>.JournalEntryPage.<pageId>]`.
- External: standard `<a href>`.

